meta {
  name: 5 - Vary Accept format
  type: http
  seq: 5
}

get {
  url: {{baseUrl}}/courses
  body: none
  auth: none
}

headers {
  Accept: application/json
}

docs {
  Exercise 6 test — Vary header:
  1. GET /courses with Accept: application/ld+json → MISS then HIT
  2. GET /courses with Accept: application/json (this request) → MISS or HIT?

  Varnish stores separate variants by Vary header (here Accept).
  Same URL, different format = different cache entry.
}
